    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Mounting Engine on Engine Stand - Mounting
        Engine on Engine Stand
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Mounting Engine on Engine Stand</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <figure id="f3900002" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figN10/N10002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Engine Stand and Engine Stand Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Stand</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Class 10.9 M10 bolt (4)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Stand Bracket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use a minimum three ton rated chain hoist, equipped with
                        safety hooks to lift the engine from factory installed lifting eyes.
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, use metric Class 10.9 or SAE grade 8 bolts when mounting
                        the Engine Mounting Bracket to the engine and Engine Stand. See instructions included with
                        Engine Stand and Engine Mounting Bracket.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift engine from factory installed lifting eyes using a minimum three ton rated chain
                    hoist equipped with safety hooks.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_47.xml" xrefid="t390000203">Engine Stand Bracket</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390000203"/>
                    holes with bolt holes in the right side of the crankcase and install four Class 10.9 M10 bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten four M10 bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque
                        <xref refid="S300GTG"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise or lower the engine to the approximate height of the
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_47.xml" xrefid="t390000203">Engine Stand</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="t390000203"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount engine and Engine Stand Bracket on the Engine Stand using four Class 10.9 M16
                    bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten M16 engine stand bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_373.xml" xrefid="S300GTG">standard torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="S300GTG"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slowly release tension from engine hoist.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hoist safety chain hooks from engine lifting eyes.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
